  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "If you have forgotten your SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) password, you can follow these steps to reset it:\n\n1. **Visit the official SSC website:** Go to the official website of the Staff Selection Commission (https://ssc.nic.in).\n\n2. **Click on the Login Section:** Look for the login section, usually found at the top right corner of the homepage.\n\n3. **Forgot Password:** Click on the \u201cForgot Password\u201d or \u201cReset Password\u201d link. This link is typically available in the login area.\n\n4. **Enter Details:** You will need to provide certain details, such as your registration number, date of birth, and possibly other personal information that you provided during your application process.\n\n5. **Receive Reset Link:** After submitting the required information, check your registered email address and/or mobile number for a password reset link or OTP (One-Time Password).\n\n6. **Follow Instructions:** Click on the link or enter the OTP to proceed. Follow the instructions to create a new password.\n\n7. **Log In:** Once you have successfully reset your password, you can log in to your account using the new password.\n\nIf you face any issues during the process, you can contact the SSC helpdesk or support for further assistance.",
